                <span class="app-c-publisher-metadata__definition-sentence">
                  <a class="govuk-link" href="/government/organisations/sellafield-ltd">Sellafield Ltd</a>
                </span>
            </dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
  </div>

    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>




<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds content-bottom-margin">
    <div class="responsive-bottom-margin">
      <figure class="app-c-figure" lang="en">
  <img class="app-c-figure__image" src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/image_data/file/111044/s300_Bus_Station_-_jpg.jpg" alt="The Bus Station in Whitehaven"></img>
    <figcaption class="app-c-figure__figcaption">
        <p class="app-c-figure__figcaption-text">
          The Bus Station in Whitehaven
        </p>

    </figcaption>
</figure>

      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
    
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Our head of community and development, Gary McKeating, recently toured the site and took the opportunity to dispel some myths about the project.</p>

<p>He said:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Some people think that the Bus Station is just another office for Sellafield workers, and that the building will be home to a pub. But the truth is so much more exciting than that.</p>

  <p class="last-child"><a rel="external" href="https://youtu.be/-HKznFc9VFg" class="govuk-link">The Bus Station</a></p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>The offices will be home to creative and digital businesses, not to Sellafield employees. A space where new businesses can set up their base and thrive.</p>

  <p>Downstairs in the building will be The Peddler which will cater to people all day, whether you’re looking for somewhere to have breakfast, somewhere to hold a business meeting in the day, or looking for somewhere to have an evening meal.</p>

  <p class="last-child">It will be a great addition to what Whitehaven has to offer locals and visitors alike.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>The Bus Station will open its doors in Spring 2021.</p>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>Funded by the Nuclear Decommissioning Authority and Sellafield Ltd, the Bus Station is being delivered by BEC with support from Copeland Borough Council.</p>

<p>Local contractor Thomas Armstrong are the lead contractor on the project.</p>
</div>

</div>

</div>
